# PR 5 fixture: interpreted string literals + interpolation.
# Single-quote ("...") and empty (""). No raw strings -- those land in PR 6.
# Escape codepoints kept <= 0x7F so byte-walking and Python-codepoint-walking
# dumpers agree (UTF-8 multi-byte handling is deferred to PR 7).
""
"hi"
"a\nb\tc\\d\"e\bf"
"\xff"
"\u000041"
"x=\{n}"
"\{a + b}"
"\{f a: 1 b: 2}"
"\{{n: 1}}"
"\{"inner"}"
"end"
